{
  "video_id": "kAP8RPEX8pw",
  "title": "Financial statements - Lecture 4 Income Statement (ASPE)",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 11070.0,
      "end_time": 12510.0,
      "text": "Hi, Else here."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12510.0,
      "end_time": 15330.0,
      "text": "And in this video, we&#39;ll start exploring financial statements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 15330.0,
      "end_time": 17550.0,
      "text": "what they look like, and how they&#39;re interconnected."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 17550.0,
      "end_time": 19560.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll be using ASPE, Accounting Standards"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 19560.0,
      "end_time": 22440.0,
      "text": "for Private Enterprises, to produce our statements."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22440.0,
      "end_time": 24670.0,
      "text": "Why are financial statements necessary?"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 24670.0,
      "end_time": 27370.0,
      "text": "Remember that external stakeholders, mainly investors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 27370.0,
      "end_time": 29070.0,
      "text": "lenders, and other creditors, have"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 29070.0,
      "end_time": 31410.0,
      "text": "to make decisions about resource allocations--"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 31410.0,
      "end_time": 32790.0,
      "text": "where to put their money."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 32790.0,
      "end_time": 35100.0,
      "text": "They use financial statements to answer questions"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 35100.0,
      "end_time": 37170.0,
      "text": "that they may have about a business."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 37170.0,
      "end_time": 38940.0,
      "text": "From the video on business organization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 38940.0,
      "end_time": 42180.0,
      "text": "we know that corporations can be either public or private."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 42180.0,
      "end_time": 44820.0,
      "text": "Public corporations must follow IFRS."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 44820.0,
      "end_time": 48340.0,
      "text": "Private corporations can follow either IFRS or ASPE."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 48340.0,
      "end_time": 50550.0,
      "text": "A private corporation that follows ASPE"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 50550.0,
      "end_time": 53220.0,
      "text": "will produce the following financial statements-- income"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 53220.0,
      "end_time": 55360.0,
      "text": "statement, statement if retained earnings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 55360.0,
      "end_time": 58140.0,
      "text": "balance sheet, and the statement of cash flows."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 58140.0,
      "end_time": 61470.0,
      "text": "Corporations who follow IFRS, whether public or private,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 61470.0,
      "end_time": 64269.0,
      "text": "must produce the following statements-- income statement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 64269.00000000001,
      "end_time": 65790.0,
      "text": "statement of comprehensive income,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 65790.0,
      "end_time": 67620.0,
      "text": "statement of changes in equity, statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 67620.0,
      "end_time": 70350.0,
      "text": "of financial position, and finally, the statement of cash"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 70350.0,
      "end_time": 71100.0,
      "text": "flows."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 71100.0,
      "end_time": 73230.0,
      "text": "If you wish to learn more about these statements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 73230.0,
      "end_time": 75603.0,
      "text": "go to my video on IFRS financial statements."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 75603.0,
      "end_time": 79200.0,
      "text": "In these videos, we&#39;ll only be covering ASPE."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 79200.0,
      "end_time": 81690.0,
      "text": "Statements must be completed in a specific order"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 81690.0,
      "end_time": 83970.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;ll start with the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 83970.0,
      "end_time": 85950.0,
      "text": "An income statement reports the results"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 85950.0,
      "end_time": 88800.0,
      "text": "of a businesses day-to-day operations-- the revenues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 88800.0,
      "end_time": 91530.0,
      "text": "less the expenses incurred to generate that revenue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 91530.0,
      "end_time": 94237.0,
      "text": "to obtain a profit figure called net income."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 94237.0,
      "end_time": 96570.0,
      "text": "The income statement measures the business&#39;s performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 96570.0,
      "end_time": 99180.0,
      "text": "within a period of time either annually, quarterly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 99180.0,
      "end_time": 99890.0,
      "text": "or monthly."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 99890.0,
      "end_time": 101640.0,
      "text": "To better understand the income statement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 101640.0,
      "end_time": 104310.0,
      "text": "we have to understand the two main elements-- revenues"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 104310.0,
      "end_time": 105540.0,
      "text": "and expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 105540.0,
      "end_time": 108300.0,
      "text": "Revenues are the income that a business earns."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 108300.0,
      "end_time": 110310.0,
      "text": "There are only two ways to earn revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 110310.0,
      "end_time": 113040.0,
      "text": "Businesses either provide a service or a good."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 113040.0,
      "end_time": 115650.0,
      "text": "The key to revenue is that it must be earned."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 115650.0,
      "end_time": 116800.0,
      "text": "What does that mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 116800.0,
      "end_time": 118950.0,
      "text": "It means that the business has done their job--"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 118950.0,
      "end_time": 120070.0,
      "text": "past tense."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 120070.0,
      "end_time": 121770.0,
      "text": "For example, if a lawn care business"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 121770.0,
      "end_time": 123840.0,
      "text": "plans to mow a customer&#39;s lawn tomorrow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 123840.0,
      "end_time": 126600.0,
      "text": "it has not earned revenue today, because they have not"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 126600.0,
      "end_time": 127817.0,
      "text": "done their job as yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 127817.0,
      "end_time": 129900.0,
      "text": "After they&#39;ve finished mowing the customer&#39;s lawn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 129900.0,
      "end_time": 131310.0,
      "text": "they have earned their revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 131310.0,
      "end_time": 133940.0,
      "text": "If a retail store plans to sell a product to a customer"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 133940.0,
      "end_time": 137310.0,
      "text": "tomorrow, revenue is not earned because, again, the business"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 137310.0,
      "end_time": 139380.0,
      "text": "has not as yet done their job."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 139380.0,
      "end_time": 141810.0,
      "text": "Revenues can only be recognized when the business has"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 141810.0,
      "end_time": 145600.0,
      "text": "finished the job, provided the service, or delivered the good."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 145600.0,
      "end_time": 146880.0,
      "text": "Notice the past tense--"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 146880.0,
      "end_time": 149580.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s very important with regards to the element revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 149580.0,
      "end_time": 151530.0,
      "text": "To summarize, revenue is income earned"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 151530.0,
      "end_time": 153600.0,
      "text": "through the day-to-day activities of a business"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 153600.0,
      "end_time": 156000.0,
      "text": "when a service or good is provided."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 156000.0,
      "end_time": 159090.0,
      "text": "Revenue-- earned by providing services or goods."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 159090.0,
      "end_time": 160920.0,
      "text": "Expenses or the cost of the resources"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 160920.0,
      "end_time": 163020.0,
      "text": "that have been used, consumed, or incurred to help"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 163020.0,
      "end_time": 164100.0,
      "text": "generate revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 164100.0,
      "end_time": 166620.0,
      "text": "Expenses are best described through an example."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 166620.0,
      "end_time": 169770.0,
      "text": "If you use gas in a lawnmower when you move a customer&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 169770.0,
      "end_time": 172320.0,
      "text": "lawn, then the gas that was consumed during the moving"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 172320.0,
      "end_time": 174230.0,
      "text": "of the lawn is an expense--"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 174230.0,
      "end_time": 176100.0,
      "text": "a cost to earn the revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 176100.0,
      "end_time": 176850.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 176850.0,
      "end_time": 178830.0,
      "text": "Because the gas was consumed in order to help"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 178830.0,
      "end_time": 180510.0,
      "text": "generate service revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 180510.0,
      "end_time": 182940.0,
      "text": "Note that the concept of used, consumed, or incurred"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 182940.0,
      "end_time": 185760.0,
      "text": "is important, but so is the fact that these things must"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 185760.0,
      "end_time": 187800.0,
      "text": "have happened in order to earn revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 187800.0,
      "end_time": 190530.0,
      "text": "Costs or expenses must be matched to the revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 190530.0,
      "end_time": 191760.0,
      "text": "they helped to generate."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 191760.0,
      "end_time": 195060.0,
      "text": "Expenses-- cost of what is used, consumed, or incurred to help"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 195060.0,
      "end_time": 196171.0,
      "text": "generate revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 196171.0,
      "end_time": 197670.0,
      "text": "Now that you understand the elements"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 197670.0,
      "end_time": 199120.0,
      "text": "that make up the income statement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 199120.0,
      "end_time": 200670.0,
      "text": "let&#39;s look at the format."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 200670.0,
      "end_time": 202865.0,
      "text": "The format of an income statement is important."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 202865.0,
      "end_time": 204240.0,
      "text": "Note that the heading must always"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 204240.0,
      "end_time": 205920.0,
      "text": "include the company name, the title"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 205920.0,
      "end_time": 208590.0,
      "text": "of the financial statement, and the time period covered."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 208590.0,
      "end_time": 210222.0,
      "text": "Then revenues are listed first."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 210222.0,
      "end_time": 211680.0,
      "text": "If there are multiple revenues, you"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 211680.0,
      "end_time": 213870.0,
      "text": "must list each different type of revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 213870.0,
      "end_time": 217170.0,
      "text": "individually, and then show a subtotal called total revenues."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 217170.0,
      "end_time": 219330.0,
      "text": "Is there a correct order for revenues?"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 219330.0,
      "end_time": 222000.0,
      "text": "Generally, they&#39;re placed in the order of magnitude-- meaning"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 222000.0,
      "end_time": 223830.0,
      "text": "from the highest amount to the lowest."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 223830.0,
      "end_time": 224550.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 224550.0,
      "end_time": 226920.0,
      "text": "Because remember the purpose of financial reporting--"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 226920.0,
      "end_time": 228720.0,
      "text": "provide information for external users"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 228720.0,
      "end_time": 230820.0,
      "text": "to make resource allocation decisions."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 230820.0,
      "end_time": 233220.0,
      "text": "Therefore, highlighting the larger sources of revenue"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 233220.0,
      "end_time": 235860.0,
      "text": "first help to make the information more understandable"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 235860.0,
      "end_time": 237450.0,
      "text": "and increases clarity."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 237450.0,
      "end_time": 239760.0,
      "text": "Expenses are listed next with the heading called"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 239760.0,
      "end_time": 241230.0,
      "text": "operating expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 241230.0,
      "end_time": 243300.0,
      "text": "The order of expenses, similar to revenues,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 243300.0,
      "end_time": 244894.0,
      "text": "are from the largest to the smallest."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 244894.0,
      "end_time": 246810.0,
      "text": "After listing all the expenses, this statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 246810.0,
      "end_time": 248700.0,
      "text": "provides a total of all the expenses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 248700.0,
      "end_time": 250710.0,
      "text": "excluding income tax expense."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 250710.0,
      "end_time": 253980.0,
      "text": "Next is the subtotal-- income before income tax expense"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 253980.0,
      "end_time": 257190.0,
      "text": "calculated as total revenue minus total expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 257190.0,
      "end_time": 260370.0,
      "text": "Then, income tax expense is a separate expense item"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 260370.0,
      "end_time": 262830.0,
      "text": "before listing a final net income amount."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 262830.0,
      "end_time": 265800.0,
      "text": "Often, textbooks show income tax expense in the same listing"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 265800.0,
      "end_time": 267310.0,
      "text": "as operating expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 267310.0,
      "end_time": 268920.0,
      "text": "However, this is incorrect."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 268920.0,
      "end_time": 271380.0,
      "text": "Operating expenses are the costs of operating the business"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 271380.0,
      "end_time": 274680.0,
      "text": "and are controllable, for the most part, by the business."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 274680.0,
      "end_time": 277470.0,
      "text": "Income tax expense is prescribed by this CRA--"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 277470.0,
      "end_time": 281490.0,
      "text": "Canada Revenue Agency-- and is not at all controllable."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 281490.0,
      "end_time": 283440.0,
      "text": "As a consequence, income tax expense"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 283440.0,
      "end_time": 285170.0,
      "text": "must be listed separately."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 285170.0,
      "end_time": 287670.0,
      "text": "What happens if expenses are greater than revenues?"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 287670.0,
      "end_time": 289950.0,
      "text": "Then a net loss amount is provided that the bottom"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 289950.0,
      "end_time": 290971.0,
      "text": "of the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 290971.0,
      "end_time": 292470.0,
      "text": "The statement we have developed here"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 292470.0,
      "end_time": 294344.0,
      "text": "is called the single step income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 294344.0,
      "end_time": 296010.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll be covering a multiple step income"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 296010.0,
      "end_time": 297810.0,
      "text": "statement in a future video."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 297810.0,
      "end_time": 299547.0,
      "text": "Remember to pause the video to determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 299547.0,
      "end_time": 301380.0,
      "text": "your answer to this check your understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 301380.0,
      "end_time": 304320.0,
      "text": "question about the uses of the income statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 304320.0,
      "end_time": 306930.0,
      "text": "Investors are interested in a business&#39;s past performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 306930.0,
      "end_time": 308137.0,
      "text": "because it helps them."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 311800.0,
      "end_time": 313440.0,
      "text": "The answer is not A--"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 313440.0,
      "end_time": 315720.0,
      "text": "determining the amount of debt a business currently"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 315720.0,
      "end_time": 318180.0,
      "text": "has is answered by reviewing the balance sheet."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 318180.0,
      "end_time": 319830.0,
      "text": "The answer is not B either--"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 319830.0,
      "end_time": 322300.0,
      "text": "as the current value of a businesses property, plant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 322300.0,
      "end_time": 325560.0,
      "text": "and equipment is not available on any financial statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 325560.0,
      "end_time": 327510.0,
      "text": "that is produced under ASPE."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 327510.0,
      "end_time": 329070.0,
      "text": "The answer is not D either."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 329070.0,
      "end_time": 331110.0,
      "text": "Determining if a business is profitable enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 331110.0,
      "end_time": 333720.0,
      "text": "to repay its debt is what lenders and creditors"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 333720.0,
      "end_time": 336270.0,
      "text": "will use the income statement for, not investors."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 336270.0,
      "end_time": 338520.0,
      "text": "The correct answer is C as investors"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 338520.0,
      "end_time": 340920.0,
      "text": "are interested in determining the future profitability"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 340920.0,
      "end_time": 341920.0,
      "text": "of the business."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 341920.0,
      "end_time": 342690.0,
      "text": "Why is this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 342690.0,
      "end_time": 344700.0,
      "text": "Because it will help investors determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 344700.0,
      "end_time": 346770.0,
      "text": "if they will get the return on their investment"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 346770.0,
      "end_time": 348300.0,
      "text": "that they want in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 348300.0,
      "end_time": 349967.0,
      "text": "Investors also use the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 349967.0,
      "end_time": 352050.0,
      "text": "to determine if the business will be in a position"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 352050.0,
      "end_time": 353239.0,
      "text": "to pay dividends."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 353239.0,
      "end_time": 355530.0,
      "text": "Lenders use the income statement to help them determine"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 355530.0,
      "end_time": 357660.0,
      "text": "if they want to fund a business with loans"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 357660.0,
      "end_time": 360420.0,
      "text": "and if the business will be in a position to repay the loan"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 360420.0,
      "end_time": 362280.0,
      "text": "plus interest in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 362280.0,
      "end_time": 363780.0,
      "text": "Other creditors use this statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 363780.0,
      "end_time": 366071.0,
      "text": "to figure out if the business will be profitable enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 366071.0,
      "end_time": 367920.0,
      "text": "to repay their debts as they come due."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 367920.0,
      "end_time": 369750.0,
      "text": "The long-term survival of any business"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 369750.0,
      "end_time": 372060.0,
      "text": "depends on its ability to produce revenues that are"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 372060.0,
      "end_time": 373830.0,
      "text": "greater than their expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 373830.0,
      "end_time": 376470.0,
      "text": "Profit allows a business to fund their financing activities"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 376470.0,
      "end_time": 378930.0,
      "text": "by paying dividends to shareholders and interest"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 378930.0,
      "end_time": 379800.0,
      "text": "to lenders."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 379800.0,
      "end_time": 382680.0,
      "text": "It also allows the business to pay for investing activities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 382680.0,
      "end_time": 384090.0,
      "text": "like buying new equipment."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 384090.0,
      "end_time": 386100.0,
      "text": "Investors and creditors base their decisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 386100.0,
      "end_time": 388770.0,
      "text": "on their beliefs about a business&#39;s future performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 388770.0,
      "end_time": 391050.0,
      "text": "Income statements, which show past performance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 391050.0,
      "end_time": 393840.0,
      "text": "give stakeholders information to help them make predictions"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 393840.0,
      "end_time": 395562.0,
      "text": "about future profitability."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 395562.0,
      "end_time": 397020.0,
      "text": "The income statement is a statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 397020.0,
      "end_time": 399660.0,
      "text": "that is connected to two other financial statements."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 399660.0,
      "end_time": 402420.0,
      "text": "The net income or net loss from the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 402420.0,
      "end_time": 404880.0,
      "text": "is used in both the statement of retained earnings"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 404880.0,
      "end_time": 407670.0,
      "text": "and the statement of cash flows under the indirect method."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 407670.0,
      "end_time": 409620.0,
      "text": "Since the net income from the income statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 409620.0,
      "end_time": 411240.0,
      "text": "is used in other statements, it&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 411240.0,
      "end_time": 413430.0,
      "text": "always the first financial statement completed."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 413430.0,
      "end_time": 415500.0,
      "text": "The next statement produced is the statement"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 415500.0,
      "end_time": 416730.0,
      "text": "of retained earnings."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 416730.0,
      "end_time": 420110.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll be covering that statement in our next video."
    }
  ]
}